  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Treat 60,000 children in rural Zimbabwe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Upenyu has treated about 5,000 school-children in rural Zimbabwe for parasitic worm diseases, such as schistosomiasis.  These diseases cause severe morbidity in children, including bleeding, stunted growth, impaired cognitive development, and poor school performance.  It is our hope that, by providing treatment, children become happy and productive members of society.</narrative>
  </description>
